                <h2>Letter O</h2>
                <p>The 'O' in ASL is formed by bringing all fingers together and touching the thumb to the fingertips,
                    creating a circular shape. This sign visually resembles the letter 'O' and is straightforward but
                    requires a clear and distinct formation.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Initial Hand Position:</strong> Start with your hand open, palm facing yourself, fingers
                        slightly apart.</li>
                    <li><strong>Forming the Circle:</strong> Curl your fingers towards your palm and touch your thumb to
                        the tips of your fingers. The fingers should come together to form a circle or 'O' shape.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ensure Clarity:</strong> Make sure the circle is complete with no gaps between the thumb
                        and fingers. The shape should be round and visible, clearly representing the letter 'O'.</li>
                    <li><strong>Steady Hand:</strong> Keep your hand steady while forming the 'O' to maintain the
                        shape's integrity. The sign should be held at eye level for visibility.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Practicing the 'O' sign is important for its universal use in finger spelling. Repeat the formation
                    several times to ensure it's easily recognizable and distinct.</p>
